name: Use useCallback for event handlers
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Event handlers passed to child components without useCallback
then: Wrap event handlers in useCallback with proper dependencies
why: Prevents unnecessary re-renders of child components when parent re-renders.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use useMemo for expensive calculations
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Expensive calculations without memoization
then: Use useMemo to cache calculation results
why: Prevents recalculating expensive operations on every render.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use React.memo for expensive components
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Expensive components without memoization
then: Wrap components in React.memo to prevent unnecessary re-renders
why: React.memo prevents re-rendering when props haven't changed.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper loading states
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without loading indicators for async operations
then: Use loading states from custom hooks and display CircularProgress or skeletons
why: Loading states improve perceived performance and user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Optimize Material-UI imports
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Importing entire Material-UI libraries
then: Import specific components to reduce bundle size
why: Tree shaking reduces bundle size and improves load times.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use lazy loading for routes
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: Large components loaded eagerly
then: Use React.lazy() for route-based code splitting
why: Lazy loading reduces initial bundle size and improves load times.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement request deduplication
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: API calls that could be duplicated
then: Implement request deduplication in custom hooks
why: Prevents duplicate API calls and improves performance.
globs: ["frontend/src/hooks/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Use optimistic updates
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: Mutations without optimistic updates
then: Implement optimistic updates for better perceived performance
why: Optimistic updates make the UI feel more responsive.
globs: ["frontend/src/hooks/**/*.ts", "frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Monitor bundle size
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: Large bundle sizes without monitoring
then: Use bundle analyzer and monitor bundle size
why: Bundle size directly impacts load times and user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper dependency arrays
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: useEffect or useCallback with missing or incorrect dependencies
then: Include all dependencies in dependency arrays
why: Proper dependencies prevent stale closures and ensure correct behavior.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use skeleton loading
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: Simple loading spinners for complex content
then: Use skeleton components that match the actual content structure
why: Skeleton loading provides better perceived performance and user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

